reviews.title: Nice place for lunch. Good service. VFM.
reviews.text: Called in for lunch on a Monday afternoon. Spotlessly clean, great service, good value for money and a good selection. Recommend.

reviews.title: Good visit
reviews.text: The food was really good with good portion sizes, the restaurant also took special wishes, it was a little bit too warm inside but manageable, the service was a little slow

reviews.title: Keep quality control and maybe taste it yourself
reviews.text:
Everything actually perfect though
But look ff at the still edible ice cream coupe
With 3 people for dessert had a red fruit ice cream and about 3 hours later it was fighting to get a place at the toilet
All 3 ice cream coupes were in the toilet later
Too bad but unfortunately

reviews.title: Hasty stuff. Like you have to leave v them
reviews.text:
Latte macchiato fine just like the carrot cake Toilet neat but my negativity is in the service.
Think of my remark more as a tip: as soon as your cake is finished, the plate is already pulled away from your table. This doesn't feel good.  Especially when it is also said: can I do anything for you while my glass is still 1/4 full. It makes you feel like you're being looked away! Think it's better to just let someone sit down without pulling stuff away if you still have coffee. My spoon took them too. I chased it and asked for a new spoon. Not nice like that.

reviews.title: As hospitality is meant to be!
reviews.text: Delicious salmon and a pizza eaten from the brick oven, alcohol-free also nice options to drink with it. Furthermore, an enthusiastic and cooperative ministry. This is highly recommended!

reviews.title: Bad experience.
reviews.text:
What a terrible food.
Tournedos was tough and not hot.
Vegetable was not warm and almost raw.
Besides, way too pricey.
Only the wine was good.

reviews.title: Great eatery!
reviews.text: After having a nice lunch here earlier this week, now also dined. The busy, but atmospheric place is cozy. The young service works fine. Tuna as a starter: great piece of fish with tasty entourage. The pasta dishes were also delicious in taste. Nice glass of wine with it... In short: a great eatery!

reviews.text: The service was really top, the atmosphere optimal. Here they understand how to do it. Great food and something for everyone!! We will definitely be back regularly. Highly recommended if you are near Epe.

reviews.title: Disappointing
reviews.text:
Smacking a few pieces of cooked chicken breast in a cowardly cream sauce on a sandwich and calling it pulled chicken is really not okay. It was also very little, but because it was not tasty, also not eaten. 
I was served a different drink than I ordered, and when I alerted the waitress to that, she shrugged, customer-friendly is different. I ended up paying for the drink I didn't get because it was cheaper than what I was served. 
The fries were obviously crunched a second time in the fryer before it was served. It was dark and very hard.

mgmtResponse.text:

After a long time, we tried again to see what it is like, but the service is still substandard.
You almost have to beg for a drink or snack.
The waiter walks by and sees that all the glasses are empty but does not ask if anything is wanted.
You always have to go to the waiter yourself to ask if you can get anything.
This was the last time for us, what a bad intention

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

tripContent.title: The Wanderer's guide to Saudi Arabia
tripContent.description: "When Laviai, Marsha, and I set out for Saudi Arabia with "The Wanderer" we had no idea how much this journey would change us. We expected stunning landscapes, rich history, and great food—but what we didn’t expect was how deeply we’d connect with the country and its people. From the moment we arrived, we were met with kindness and curiosity, and when we left, it felt as if we were saying goodbye to a home we'd only just discovered. This guide is our way of sharing our firsthand experiences. Whether you're planning your first visit or just curious about what makes Saudi Arabia so special, we hope our perspectives help you see this country with wide eyes, open hearts, and an endless sense of wonder." – Lina

tripContent.title: Chase horizons and conquer trails across Nevada’s rugged backcountry
tripContent.description: Nevada’s wild places were made for those who move at their own pace. Wander through desert canyons, alpine lakes, and ancient rock formations, all in one trip. Whether you're chasing stars in a dark sky park or breathing deep in the high mountains, this is the untamed side of the Silver State, ready to be roamed, hiked, and discovered.

reviews.title: Cozy and very good restaurant with enthusiastic staff
reviews.text:
We regularly visit Cornelis and it is always a pleasant experience. Enthusiastic staff and very nicely prepared food. The pizzas are really unique, fusion and yet Italian. A creative kitchen.
The only tip we have is that the map could be updated a little more often.

mgmtResponse.text: Bedankt Renate voor uw review! Fijn om te lezen dat alles naar wens is geweest. Wij importeren ons speciale Pinsa Roma meel vanuit Italie om onze eigen pizzabollen mee te maken. Vorige week hebben wij ons 3 gangen keuze menu aangepast met onder andere een wild gerecht, komt u deze ook eens bij ons proberen? Graag tot een volgende keer.

reviews.title: With Cor at Cornelis, what a combination!
reviews.text: Super friendly employees, pleasant atmosphere, nice varied menu. As a starter, the spicy prawns are delicious. Grandma's preserving jar is not to be missed and I was tempted by a delicious dessert with vanilla ice cream, espresso with Likor43, very nicely presented. If we lived closer, we would visit more often. Had a nice evening.

mgmtResponse.text: Bedankt voor uw review! Heel erg fijn om te lezen dat jullie een leuke ervaring hebben gehad bij Cornelis. Hopelijk komen jullie nog weer eens in de buurt zodat we jullie kunnen verwelkomen.

Moreover, dogs were allowed!!! That's really not possible in a restaurant. Put it on the terrace outside. Nasty and disturbing to other guests, especially if they also start barking.

reviews.title: Very good, as usual
reviews.text: This has become our favorite restaurant if we are in this part of Holland. They have an interesting menu and so far we have never been disappointed with the food ordered. Staff is always very friendly and efficient. This month' special (venison) is excellent. Good piece of well prepared meat and really nice side dishes. The meatball remains a favorite (but you need to order additional side dishes as it is not a complete meal).

reviews.title: Super gezellig!
reviews.text: This place is a very nice surprise in a place like Epe. The entourage is genuinely nice, a modern grand cafe indeed. We just moved here and already went multiple times for tea, drinks or dinner. It’s always filled with people and we always walk away happy. They have a great assortment of (vegan!) cakes to go with your tea/coffee, nice warm (Dutch) snacks to go with your drinks, and dinner is straightforward & simple but very tasty. Prices are super reasonable. Its a suitable place to bring your kids, and our dog was allowed in too when we went for tea once. We love the (carpaccio!) pizza’s - they also do take away btw - but anyone can find something they like on the menu really. Oh and have a look at the gin tonic menu. For 3 courses plus drinks we spent around 30 euro a person, which is a very good deal for the service and food quality that you get. I recommend to make a reservation..!

mgmtResponse.text:

Hope to see you again soon!

reviews.title: Good food
reviews.text: Even though not an Italian restaurant, the pizza is better than us being served in the average Italian restaurant. A decent crust with good and honest ingredients. Also the meatball was very tasty. Combined with friendly staff and a nice decor, this is a restaurant to return to. Prices are very reasonable.

reviews.title: Lovely Dinner in Epe
reviews.text:
I recently had my birthday dinner in Cornelis. As usual the setting food and staff were all amazing. They provided vegan options and it was delish. Have been every time I visit family and will definitely return. 
Enjoy!

reviews.title: The perfect place to relax and enjoy good food and fine surroundings.
reviews.text: Cornelis was recommended to us and we absolutely loved it there.  The food was excellent, the staff were polite and considerate.  We sat out on the terrace as it was a sunny evening, then later as it got cooler we sat in the conservatory part of the restaurant which was heel erg gezellig!

reviews.title: Lunch & Dinner
reviews.text:
My partner had lunch here & I returned for dinner with my son. 
We sat outside both times as I just love the atmosphere of the hussle & bussle of Epe. 
At night we sat under the heater which was do-able.
Service was great & friendly... Food amazingly good.

reviews.title: Slow service, nice food
reviews.text: Had to wait a long time to be served, but the wait was worth it. Lovely touch they had their own(?) beer called ‘Kornuit’.

reviews.title: Great place for a quick dinner
reviews.text: Dropped in on a whim and found kind staff getting us a nice table. Food was fast and also very good, with the salads as pleasant surprise dinners. The classic hamburger is another exemplary dish with a very good burger and some super quality fries on the side. We love this place!

reviews.title: Nice old building
reviews.text: We (4 of us) had our lunch here. It was OK but in spite of the name of my dish, it did not have any specialty and was just common. With beautiful weather you can sit on the nice terras, but also inside is a good place to sit. Prices are slightly above average.

reviews.title: Excellent food, considerate place
reviews.text: This place was quite a surprise. Looking from the outside, we expected a traditional restaurant, "bruin café"-like but the interior is surprisingly modern and trendy. We had a very nice dinner there (fish-menu and vegetarian burgers), the meals were creative, original and very good, the portions were perfect. We had been warned that they had a DJ and he would work just behind our table but he was considerate enough to start when we were having our coffee and the music was at a perfect sound level: loud enough so we could really enjoy the atmosphere but not so loud that we couldn't hear each others.

reviews.title: Great food and service
reviews.text:
Stumbled upon this great place. Excellent service (with a smile!) and great food. We had the 3 course chef's menu, and all of it was delicious. Every plate looked great, portion size was good too.

They served all of this with their excellent staff, I would highly recommend this place.

reviews.title: Food court fast and efficiently presenting food
reviews.text: Food court fast and efficiently presenting food. Healthy options and fresh prepared options. Suiting all visitors by great assortment.

reviews.title: Relaxed place with good food
reviews.text: We don't really know any places in Epe but happened to be in town around lunchtime. We were very happy to find this place open. The lunch was great and the staff was very friendly and attentive. Weather was good so we sat outside - we're a family of 5 (6yo, 3yo and 0yo) who would recommend this place.

reviews.title: Excellent food, excellent service, great atmosphere
reviews.text: After drinks on the terrace I had an excellent dinner here with friends for a very reasonable price. In spite of being crowded, service was smooth and very friendly.

reviews.title: Moving down
reviews.text:
In my first review I gave Cornelis an excellent score.
Excellent menu with excellent lamb cutlets
However today we were very much disappointed.
The menu never changes with only one meat dish ( calf cheek). No more lamb unfortunately.
Pizza quattro formaggi OK but not superb any more.
What really disturbed me was that we had to pay 1 euro extra for some extra garlic topping!!! We paid but I refused to leave a tip. 
Cornelis will really have to improve before we come back.

reviews.title: Exceptional Nice
reviews.text:
We where a little bid late and called for reservation: most welcome!
Excellent receipt, Nice people and good pizza's
Bon appetit!

reviews.title: God lunch menu, slow service
reviews.text:
Stopped here for lunch on Sunday. The town is very quite on Sunday and the restaurant only had four tables occupied. The building is quite pretty, although the rest of the town is a bit boring.  There is a nice terrace outside. 

The lunch menu is quite imaginative by Dutch standards, with  interesting salads, pasta, steaks and burgers as well as the inevitable soup and sandwiches. I had a Duck Superfood Salad, which was most enjoyable. 

The only negative was the service, which was really patchy. The two serving staff seemed to have a large number of things to do, none of which actually involved servicing customers.

reviews.title: Good food, friendly service and lovely location
reviews.text: This restaurant is location in a old building (someone told me it's the old town hall). In the summer they have a nice terrace to sit outside. The food is really good and the service very friendly. I can recommend the icecream dessert!

reviews.title: Best restaurant in Epe
reviews.text: Had a nice family dimmer here on a beautiful Tuesday eveing. Great admosphere with friendly service. Good selection of dishes, can certainly reccommend the mussels.

reviews.title: Charm and character with good food
reviews.text: Located in a building filled with charm and lots of character, this restaurant goes to offering great food, with excellent service! A comfortable environment, catering with an array of food types to suit all persons wants.

reviews.title: Beautiful
reviews.text: We came in for hot drinks and loved it. The building is gorgeous and the staff were great. It's definitely a beautiful meeting place. I'd definitely come back and recommend it to everyone!

reviews.title: Hot spot in Epe
reviews.text: Good atmosphere on a lovely spot.The only thing i don't like is the pizza too much salt. All the other products are excellent.

reviews.title: Coffee
reviews.text: Good atmosphere and lovely cup of coffee in the centre of town.      Lovely town to shop in with a bustling market selling lovely food.

reviews.title: pizza is not a pizza
reviews.text: Its a great new place on the square with other cafes and restaurants. Love it for ambiance and having a beer. Would give 4stars if it were not for the awful pizza. They themselves love it and advertise it as healthy due to using rice flour rather than wheat. But rice flour lacks taste and so does the pizza. Tastes like cardboard. My partner had a salad, and did like that.

reviews.title: Beatiful site & setting centre village Epe with a lot of potential
reviews.text:
In the old city hall of Epe Cornelus transformed an unique building into a appealing "grand cafe style"of eating out experience. The buildingis perfectly located and re-invented.
Beatifully done and decorated keeping the origin of the location in tact.
The menu is interesting, and varies from traditional dutch to tempting italian pizza's for kids.
Better meat dishes than fish , portionsizes are at the "low end of average needs", nicely presented and camouflaging the real value offered.
Too clever to be good enough in sizing. Tastewise rich in developing potential value.

reviews.title: Absolutely great
reviews.text:
From the service to the food, everything was great! 
Very personal service with attention to detail. Although it was crowded and the food took a little longer to prepare this did not bother us as we took in the great atmosphere of this renovated mansion. Decoration done in great taste with respect to the history of the building.
I chose lamb for my main course, the meat was succulent and very tasteful. Wine great and well priced.
Will definitely revisit and review again.
